##Hubei Lotus supply is in short supply, digging Lotus people are still waiting for the post

Can Not buy Hubei Lotus Root in Hubei?

Two consumers who live in Guanggu and Houhu in Wuhan complain that it is not easy to buy vegetables now, and it is even more difficult to buy Lotus root.

A fresh food supplier located in the Houhu region of Wuhan told the interface news that the price increase is definitely up. Now Lotus root products are not easy to wholesale, and consumers have to go through the order system when placing orders, and the first day is scheduled for delivery the next day, "Not only hard to buy Lotus root, what Lotus root are not good to buy, because the Lotus root farmers off the production cut off. ".

Big Supermarkets are not completely out of stock at the moment, but consumers are also having to watch their screens for replenishment times.

The head of Wuhan Qiangxin Vegetable Production and Marketing Professional Cooperative, a supplier of Hema in Wuhan, told interface news that due to the requirement of sealing villages and not allowing people to gather, Lotus root farmers can not dig Lotus roots in large areas for the time being, only a small portion of the pond near the base can be dug. The supply of Lotus root is only one or two thousand catties per day.

See soon to be "out of food" , buyers also began to tighten contact with Lotus root farmers.

Liang Rendiao of Honghu in Jingzhou, Hubei Province, owns more than 200 mu of Lotus fields. Recently, he has received more than half of the calls asking whether he can dig up a small amount of lotus fields.

"Several of the Ou diggers called me and asked if I could start digging these days. They are the main labor force in the family, and in previous years this time they had to dig for another month before they could rest, " Liang told interface news, because of the epidemic, no one dared to dig up Lotus root without being notified. He was afraid to take the risk, even though some of the workers were already pressing him.

To Dig Lotus Master, this time interval still is the season that makes money, nobody wants to miss.

Liang Rendiao introduced to the interface news, around the Spring Festival because of low temperatures, early frost, digging Lotus root harder, so this time of digging Lotus root master wages will be higher, also means that the labor costs of farmers will increase. Every day, Ouou diggers work 6-7 hours, each person diggings 300-400 catties, each catty can earn 1.1 to 1.2 yuan labor costs. Therefore, the Lotus root terminal price will also rise, the retail price in 5-6 yuan per catty.

As usual, in Liang Rendiao of the Lotus root field, digging masters do another month, to put the Lotus seedling (seed Lotus) time, they usually go home to rest for nearly a month, to the early May of the Lotus root belt began to come on the market, this is the Lotus harvest season; In July, 3537, also known as the new Lotus, comes on the market. Then, in August, the best-known Lotus root in Hong Lake can be dug up, and the work of those digging up the Lotus is done around this production cycle, until April of next year. Over and over again.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
For Liang Ren Carving Dig Lotus Root Master. Photo from the interviewee

The planting area and output of Lotus Root in Hubei ranked first in the country, with the planting area reaching more than 2 million mu, accounting for one third of the total output of Lotus rhizome. According to public information, the main lotus-producing counties in Hubei Province include Caidian District, Hanchuan, Hong Lake, Xiantao, Xishui County, Jiangxia District, east-west Lake, Yunmeng, Jianli County, Jianli County, Jiaxing and more than 10 other counties and cities.

In the past, the low-lying areas in Hong Lake, Jingzhou, where Liang's Lotus field is located, have evolved over and over again to form the soil peculiar to Qingniba in Hong Lake. This kind of soil is rich in fertility, fine and soft in texture, strong in grasping fertility and suitable for the growth of Lotus root. Therefore, Honghu Lotus root shape long, full, rich starch content. In 2015, the "Hong Lake Lotus" was registered as a geographical indication of agricultural products.

Most of the Lotus fields of Liang Rendiao are pink Lotus, a few are 3537, and some are called as ——————————————————————————————————————————————————————————. As a whole, the total output of his Lotus field is about 30 tons a year.

In previous years, Liang had dug until December twenty-eight, when he finished work at twenty-six, just after the outbreak.

If there is no epidemic, years later this time digging Lotus root master basic will continue to post. He had no idea the outbreak had lasted so long and did not know when it would end.

But Liang Rendiao told interface news, years ago has been shipped about 75% of the lotus root, the remaining amount is not too big, now there is no way to dig Lotus root operation, had to fill the lotus root pond water, slow down photosynthesis to inhibit the growth of Lotus root. If after a period of time can not be dug up, you have to keep as a lotus root.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Liang RENDIAO's Lotus field. Photo from interviewee

Compared with the farmers of Lotus Root, Zhao Ke of Hongke aquatic vegetable planting cooperative in Honghu is hardly affected. His 700 mu of Lotus root field is mainly planted with Lotus root.

According to the data of encyclopedia, the Lotus Root Belt is a young rhizome of Lotus, which consists of an internode at the top of the rhizome and a terminal bud. The Lotus root belt and Lotus rhizome are homologous organs. When the conditions are suitable, the Lotus root belt becomes the Lotus root when it expands.

The reason for not being affected is that the current season, which is the underwater growing season of the Strip, begins to harvest in may-august. Zhao branch of the Lotus root belt yield about 1500 Jin per mu, by a larger professional company in the form of purchase orders, the final flow to the food and beverage market. Haidilao is also one of these products with Lotus root, in addition to airlines, high-speed rail and other customers.

Zhao Ke told the interface news that compared with the Lotus root, the profit space in the Lotus root belt is bigger, because planting management is more troublesome, the Lotus root only needs to manage the water level, don't let the water level in the pond rise and fall by a large margin, and the Labor involved is not much, the Lotus root with 100 days of critical harvesting, harvesting every day, more labor costs.

An expert from the Jiangxia District Agricultural Bureau in Wuhan told the interface news that currently what is really affected is the Lotus root, which has a long storage period before the Spring Festival, when the harvest of the Lotus root is not much in the month after the Spring Festival, but in normal times there would be another sales spike years later.

In accordance with the past, digestion of years ago stock, most of the workers will start a new round of Lotus root digging work, the market supply of Lotus root will increase, the price will be stable.

But this year, digging Lotus root can not be employed, some buyers have bottomed out of stock, Lotus farmers back to work the requirements of the more and more urgent.

February 21, Liang Rendiao got the news, his market for this began to consider to the Lotus farmers to distribute passes, pass in the inspection and after a good deal, you can dig a small amount of Lotus root. Liang Rendiao told the interface news, these two days have begun to apply for a pass, but a day can only dig about 300 catties, his lotus root field still 50,000 catties can dig.
